

Step 1: Install AWS CLI
aws --version


Step 2: Configure Each Account with a Named Profile
Run aws configure --profile <profile-name> for each account.

Account 1
aws configure --profile account1
AWS Access Key ID
AWS Secret Access Key
Region (e.g., us-east-1)
Output format (optional, e.g., json)

Account 2
aws configure --profile account2
AWS Access Key ID
AWS Secret Access Key
Region (e.g., us-east-1)
Output format (optional, e.g., json)

Account 3
aws configure --profile account3
AWS Access Key ID
AWS Secret Access Key
Region (e.g., us-east-1)
Output format (optional, e.g., json)


Use Named Profiles in Terminal
Option 1: Use --profile flag per command
aws s3 ls --profile account1
aws ec2 describe-instances --profile account2
